# Physics regression suite: locks in the state-assertable bugs found and fixed
# during the codex/GPT-5.5 play-harness bug hunts (round set 1: R1-R4; round
# set 5: R5-1, R5-3). Each section reproduces the exact repro coordinates and
# asserts the invariant that must hold post-fix. Any failure makes the run
# exit non-zero. Run:
#   ./viewer/target/release/examples/play.exe viewer/scripts/physics-regressions.play
weather season 0.45

# ---- R1: placing a block straight down in walk mode must not embed the
# head (self-clip into the new block => ceiling reads non-none / player
# falls into a starfield void). Placing twice in a row must stay clean.
log R1 place-down must not self-clip (no ceiling, stays grounded)
teleport 1.510 40.490 0.004
look 0 -80
mode walk
wait 1
tap rmb
wait 0.2
assert ceiling_above_km none
assert grounded true
shot r1_place1
tap rmb
wait 0.2
assert ceiling_above_km none
assert grounded true
shot r1_place2

# ---- R2: fly mode with the eye below a river water surface must read
# underwater==true (was previously missing the immersion flag in fly mode).
log R2 fly below river water -> underwater true
mode fly
# Track-B's shared meander moves the thalweg ~22 m south at this reach; keep
# the regression in the same river, now over its 10 m-deep carved column.
teleport -0.4902 -30.550 0.004
assert underwater true
shot r2_fly_river

# ---- R3: a below-freezing lake is a solid ice sheet, not liquid — walking
# onto it must be grounded (not swimming) and must not report water.
log R3 frozen lake is walkable ice, not liquid
teleport 73.486 -76.450 0.004
mode walk
wait 8
assert grounded true
assert underwater false
assert has_water false
shot r3_frozen_walk

# ---- R4: after being underwater then teleporting above the lake surface in
# fly mode, underwater must clear to false immediately (was previously
# stale for a tick, leaving the underwater tint on above the surface).
log R4 teleport above lake clears stale underwater
teleport 20.633 127.615 0.05
mode walk
wait 14
assert underwater true
mode fly
teleport 20.633 127.615 0.02
assert underwater false
shot r4_above_clear

# ================= second hunt (codex round set 5) =================
# R5-3 runs FIRST on the pristine savanna column (edits persist within a run,
# so it must dig before R5-1 does): a one-block-deep dug hole must be escapable
# — walking into the rim steps the player up onto the surrounding ground
# (>= 0.548), not trapped at the 0.5476 floor.
log R5-3 escape a dug one-block hole by stepping onto the rim
teleport 1.510 40.490 0.004
look 0 -80
mode walk
wait 1
tap lmb
wait 0.5
look 0 -5
hold w 3
assert ground_km >= 0.548

# R5-1: breaking the block underfoot must not leave the player grounded in
# air — grounded must clear the instant the floor is removed, then re-settle
# on the lower support after a tick. (Reuses the same column; R5-3 already left
# a hole here and walked off, so this settles in it and digs one deeper — the
# grounded toggle holds at any depth.)
log R5-1 break underfoot -> grounded clears then re-settles
teleport 1.510 40.490 0.004
look 0 -80
mode walk
wait 1
assert grounded true
tap lmb
assert grounded false
wait 0.5
assert grounded true

# (R5-2 frozen-sea material and R5-4 dug-shaft-floor material are visual
# render fixes with no state assertion — verified by screenshot in the hunt.)
